<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Representativeness of the sample </inglise>
<eesti> Valimi representatiivsus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For a group of unemployed people representing 5 % of the working age population the relative standard error for the estimation of annual averages (or for the spring estimates in the case of an annual survey in the spring) at NUTS II level shall not exceed 8 % of the sub-population in question. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;tute r&uuml;hma puhul, kes esindab 5% t&ouml;&ouml;ealisest elanikkonnast, ei v&otilde;i suhteline standardviga NUTS II tasandil aasta keskmises arvestuses (v&otilde;i kui aastavaatlus toimub kevadel, siis kevade arvestuses) olla &uuml;le 8% asjaomasest elanikkonna alavalimist. </eesti>
<inglise> Regions with less than 300 000 inhabitants shall be exempt from this requirement. </inglise>
<eesti> See n&otilde;ue ei kehti piirkondade kohta, kus on alla 300 000 elaniku. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In the case of a continuous survey, for sub-populations which constitute 5 % of the working age population the relative standard error at national level for the estimate of changes between two successive quarters, shall not exceed 2 % of the sub-population in question. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;ealisest elanikkonnast 5% esindava alavalimi pidevuuringul ei v&otilde;i kahe j&auml;rjestikuse kvartali vahelise muutuste arvestuse suhteline standardviga riigi tasandil olla suurem kui 2% k&otilde;nealusest alavalimist. </eesti>
<inglise> For Member States with a population of between one million and twenty million inhabitants, this requirement is relaxed so that the relative standard error for the estimate of quarterly changes shall not exceed 3 % of the sub-population in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Miljoni kuni 20 miljoni elanikuga liikmesriigis ei v&otilde;i suhteline standardviga kvartali arvestuses olla suurem kui 3 % k&otilde;nealusest alavalimist. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States whose population is below one million inhabitants are exempt from these precision requirements concerning changes. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide kohta, kelle elanikkond on alla &uuml;he miljoni, k&otilde;nealsued t&auml;psusn&otilde;uded ei kehti. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the survey is carried out only in the spring, at least a quarter of the survey units are taken from the preceding survey and at least a quarter form part of the following survey. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui vaatlus tehakse ainult kevadel, peab v&auml;hemalt veerand vaatlus&uuml;ksustest p&auml;rinema eelmisest vaatlusest ja veerand olema j&auml;rgmise vaatluse osa. </eesti>
